# S2A Component Authoring

Full reference for building S2A component sets in Figma via `figma_execute`.

## Property panel order (non-negotiable)
1. Variants — State, Size, Style, Context, Orientation, Breakpoint
2. Booleans — show/hide toggles only
3. Instance Swaps — icon, media, lockup
4. Text — every designer-editable text node
5. Nested props — exposed sub-component properties (last)

## Property naming
- Property names: Title Case (`State`, `Show Icon Start`, `Label`)
- Variant values: lowercase-kebab (`default`, `hover`, `on-light`, `sm`, `md`)

## Layer naming
```
ComponentName                    ← COMPONENT_SET
  └─ State=Default, Size=Md      ← COMPONENT
       ├─ .root                  ← outermost frame
       │    ├─ .icon-start
       │    ├─ .label
       │    └─ .icon-end
       └─ [focus ring]           ← visual-only layers
```

## figma_execute mandatory patterns
1. Search for existing library components before building from scratch
2. Get text style IDs via `figma.getLocalTextStylesAsync()` before any text node
3. Load fonts at top of every script touching text nodes
4. Prefetch all variables with `Promise.all` — never `await` inside loops
5. Use `figma.variables.getVariableByIdAsync` (async)
6. Use `await figma.setCurrentPageAsync(page)` — not `figma.currentPage = page`
7. Set `layoutSizingHorizontal = 'FILL'` only after `appendChild`
8. Call `createInstance()` on a COMPONENT variant — never on a COMPONENT_SET
9. Place all components inside a named Section — never floating on canvas
